<title>Interface for Smarter Healthcare Systems</title>
<h1>Interface for Smarter Healthcare Systems</h1>

<h2>Cognos Environment</h2>

After experimenting with visualization using
IBM Many Eyes Tool,
the next level of sophistication involves setting up a Cognos
Environment.  These of course would involve setting up all the
required software and then configuring the Cognos Server to allow for
users to create visualization widgets. 

<p>
The following PDF contains four references where the IBM Cognos product was
used to help Healthcare customers.

<p>
<a href="http://public.dhe.ibm.com/software/data/sw-library/cognos/pdfs/casestudies/cs_customer_success_in_healthcare.pdf">http://public.dhe.ibm.com/software/data/sw-library/cognos/pdfs/casestudies/cs_customer_success_in_healthcare.pdf</a>.

<p>
Mercury Medical is a healthcare manufacturer that improves reporting and
analysis with IBM Cognos Express:

<p>
<a href="http://public.dhe.ibm.com/common/ssi/ecm/en/ytc03190caen/YTC03190CAEN.PDF">http://public.dhe.ibm.com/common/ssi/ecm/en/ytc03190caen/YTC03190CAEN.PDF</a>

<p>
This link does a lengthy description of why one should use Dashboards
to display healthcare data.  The PDF is mostly text but it has some
small screen shots on page 9:

<p>
<a href="http://public.dhe.ibm.com/software/data/sw-library/cognos/pdfs/whitepapers/wp_picturing_performance_ibm_cognos_dahboards_and_scorecards_for_healthcare.pdf">http://public.dhe.ibm.com/software/data/sw-library/cognos/pdfs/whitepapers/wp_picturing_performance_ibm_cognos_dahboards_and_scorecards_for_healthcare.pdf</a>.

